==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inset
<hw>In*set"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To infix.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inset</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Inset
<hw>In"set</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That which
is inserted or set in; an insertion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bookbinding)</fld> <def>One or more separate leaves
inserted in a volume before binding;</def> as: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
portion of the printed sheet in certain sizes of books which is cut off
before folding, and set into the middle of the folded sheet to complete
the succession of paging; -- also called
<altname>offcut</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A page or pages of
advertisements inserted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inseverable</ent>⟦br⟧
